    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// One incoming item from whichever model the Switch picked.\n// All four are OpenAI-compatible, so the response shape is identical.\nconst out = $input.item.json;\nconst modelRaw = out.model || 'unknown';\nconst model = modelRaw.toLowerCase();\nconst content = out.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || '';\nconst usage = out.usage || {};\n\n// EXAMPLE per-million-token rates (input / output). Replace with your provider's current published rates.\nconst COST = {\n  'moonshotai/kimi-k2.6':   { in: 1.00, out: 4.00 },\n  'zai-org/glm-5.1':        { in: 1.00, out: 4.00 },\n  'qwen/qwen3.6-plus':      { in: 0.30, out: 2.00 },\n  'minimaxai/minimax-m2.7': { in: 0.30, out: 1.20 },\n};\nconst rate = COST[model] || { in: 0, out: 0 };\nconst estCost = (usage.prompt_tokens || 0) / 1e6 * rate.in + (usage.completion_tokens || 0) / 1e6 * rate.out;\n\nreturn {\n  model_used: modelRaw,\n  content,\n  prompt_tokens: usage.prompt_tokens || null,\n  completion_tokens: usage.completion_tokens || null,\n  est_cost_usd: Number(estCost.toFixed(6)),\n};\n"
      },
      "id": "11111111-0000-0000-0000-000000000008",
      "name": "Normalize + tag cost",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [120, 240]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Task-type LLM router\n\nOne Header Auth credential (Atlas Cloud key) drives all four models.\n\n**Setup (once):**\n1. Create a **Header Auth** credential named `Atlas Cloud API` — Name: `Authorization`, Value: `Bearer YOUR_KEY`.\n2. Select it in each of the four HTTP Request nodes.\n3. Hit **Test workflow**.\n\nEdit `task_type` in the Sample input node to watch it route to a different model.\n\n**Make it a live API:** swap the *When clicking Test* trigger for a **Webhook** node, then POST `{ task_type, prompt, context_tokens }` to it.",
        "height": 320,
        "width": 360
      },
      "id": "11111111-0000-0000-0000-000000000009",
      "name": "Read me",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-960, -200]
